<TITLE> Almagro replaces Ferrero in Spain Davis Cup team </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MADRID, March 1 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Spain captain Albert Costa has called up Nicolas Almagro to replace the injured Juan Carlos Ferrero in the champions' team to face Switzerland in their Davis Cup first-round tie starting on Friday. Former world number one Ferrero, who lost to compatriot David Ferrer in the final of the Acapulco International event on Saturday, has been suffering from a wrist problem and also has a left knee injury, Costa said in a statement. Almagro, the world number 27, joins Ferrer, Tommy Robredo and Marcel Granollers for the March 5-7 home tie on clay at the bull ring in Logrono
